sequenceDiagram
    participant V as vegeta<br/>10 req/s × 60s
    participant N as Nginx :80
    participant W as Web (PHP)
    participant NS as Nginx Stream :5000
    participant PB as PgBouncer
    participant DB1 as db1 (PRIMARY) ❌
    participant DB2 as db2 (REPLICA)
    participant C as Consul Cluster

    Note over V,DB2: Starting failover test — db1 is primary

    V->>N: GET /db.php (steady 10/s)
    N->>W: proxy
    W->>NS: DB connect nginx:5000
    NS->>PB: TCP route
    PB->>DB1: query → ✅ response
    DB1-->>W: result → 200 OK
    V-->>V: Latency: ~7ms

    Note over DB1: ⏰ T+10s — docker kill db1

    DB1-->>DB1: 💀 Container killed (SIGKILL)

    rect rgb(255, 230, 200)
        Note over C,DB2: Failover window (~4-8s)
        C->>C: db1 Consul session expires
        DB2->>C: Acquire leader lock
        DB2->>DB2: 🚀 PROMOTE to primary

        V->>N: GET /db.php (during failover)
        N->>W: proxy
        W->>NS: DB connect nginx:5000
        NS->>PB: TCP route → db1 is DOWN
        NS->>PB: retry → db2 is now PRIMARY
        PB->>DB2: query → ✅ response
        DB2-->>W: result → 200 OK
        V-->>V: Latency: ~8ms
    end

    rect rgb(255, 200, 200)
        Note over V: ⚠️ One request times out
        V->>N: GET /db.php
        W->>NS: DB connect nginx:5000
        Note over NS: Connection refused / timeout
        W-->>V: ❌ 10s timeout
    end

    Note over DB2: ✅ db2 is now PRIMARY<br/>All subsequent requests succeed

    V->>N: GET /db.php (remaining 40s)
    N->>W: proxy → DB2 → ✅

    Note over V,DB2: 📊 Result: 599/600 (99.83%)<br/>1 timeout during ~8s failover window

    Note over DB1: 🔄 db1 manually restarted<br/>Patroni auto-rejoined as REPLICA<br/>Streaming replication from db2
